content.description: Pull a small roof at the second bolt then vertical face climbing above.  If I remember this route goes straight over the small roof and Ralph's song pulls the right side starting in the crack.  Shares anchors with Ralph's Song.
content.location: As you traverse right along the base of the crag it's the first climb  right around the corner from the dihedral with the 2 pitch "adventure climb".  Just left of Ralph's Song.

content.description: Casual start to dual cruxes with a rest in between. Shares anchor with the route on the arete to the right.
Too the right of Chipâ€™s Ahoy. Starts on a crack and goes up and slightly to the left.
content.protection: Bolts that lead up to the Anchors.

content.description: Start 60 feet right of Pet Piranha, just left of a large chimney.  Fun underclings and sidepulls to pull small roof mid route.

This is the warm up at the cliffs.  Start on a 80 degree face left of a cave-like feature and then pull a roof between the 2nd and 3rd bolt on decent lieback jugs. Continue up the face for 5 or so more bolts with a couple more tricky moves, including 2 mantles.
content.location: The first climb you come to after traversing west along the cliff band for a few hundred yards. Look for a small roof with a crack of sorts in it next to a bigger overhang.

content.description: Another cool face climb at the cliffs. Lieback the huge boulder past a bolt to its top, then up the thin face with some stemming moves to relieve the pump.
content.location: This is located in the 1st major area of climbs you come to at the cliffs. Starts in the huge crack between the wall and the 15 foot boulder.

content.description: Climb on pockets, crimps and the occasional jug.  The crux is getting over the small roof.  Great climb!  Worthwhile for sure.
content.location: This climb is to the left of the giant block (pickled eel) on the obvious pocketed and crimpy vertical face  This face is to the right of the obvious crack climb 'Line of Duty'. After the last bolt, traverse to the anchors for 'pickled eel'.

content.description: Small pockets and good side pulls.  Crux is near second to last bolt stay right and look for good side pulls.
content.location: Route is located in the most southern part of the crag.  It is the second climb from the right side of the wall and starts right of a large bulge.

climbs.name: Out of Sight, Out of Mind

content.description: Easy climbing leads to a ledge. Head straight up to some fun, tricky moves.
content.location: The next route to the right of Pickled Eel.

content.description: 10ft right of Line of Duty.  Shares start with Notamatic, but ends on Line of Duty anchors. Quality vertical limestone.
Quality line.  Same start as Oughtamatic, but stay right past small roof near the top.  Shares anchors with Psychotectonics.
content.location: From the obvious wide crack (Bark) head right 40 feet around the corner to a small buttress w/ quality rock. Routes left to right: The Cross (11c), Line of Duty(10d), Oughtamatic/Notamatic (11d same start), Pyschotectonics (12a), Pickled Eel (11a).

content.description: The only true crack in Logan Canyon!
Vertical face climb 15 feet right of Ralph's Song. Start right of first bolt then move up and left.

The best 11d in Logan Canyon. Climb steep juggy terrain in a dihedral with a crack over a bulge to a huge cereal bowl pocket out left, then up the crack and chimney with a zesty traverse at the top out left to the chains.
content.location: The furthest climb west on the crag. Look for a steep dihedral with flat belay stance.

content.description: Start 10 feet right of Master Beta.  Climb past a flake to the face above staying left of and occasionally using the crack.

What I think is the most fun climb at the cliffs. Really positive pockets and crimps leads to a bomber rest before the crux of insecure lieback slapping on a slopey arete to the chains. Only 5 bolts but its full value.
content.location: Located 3 routes left of pickled eel on the major steep pocketed and featured wall. Just right of the arete.

content.description: 10 feet to the right, this is a more direct start to Pet Piranha.  A couple hard moves over a steep bulge, including a dead point to a two finger crimp w/ poor feet, define this route.  Finishes on Pet Piranha.
Start up obvious 12" crack, traverse left under black roof (pretty fun), pull roof and climb good edges to the top.
content.location: Look for the obvious wide crack splitting the face (has anyone ever climbed this?).  The Route climbs just to the left of it.

content.description:
A two to three pitch natural pro route.  A little grungy, but I thought it was worth the adventure.

P1:  Start in the Right facing dihedral. Climb to the top of a large ledge.  (80 Ft)

P2: I can't remember exactly when but it seems like eventually you pull out of the corner and climb up discontinuous cracks on the face to the right. Up to a sloping belay ledge with one bolt and a good crack to belay in.  Pretty Fun if you can dodge the loose rock. (80ft)

P3: Follow obvious thin crack up over bulge to the top.  Best pitch on the climb. Kind of tricky. (80 ft)

Descent: 2 rappels w/ two ropes.  Bring some webbing.
content.protection: Double set of cams, nuts, and long runners.
content.location: In the gully before you get to Utah Beta and Ralph's Song.  Climbs large tower shaped formation with big right facing dihedral
